				<li><a name="f28" id="f28"></a>For a full description of the Russian invasion  of Georgian territories, <em>see</em>, Philip  Pan, Jonathan Finer, <em>Russia Says Two  Regions in Georgia Are Independent</em>, WASHINGTON POST, Aug. 27, 2008, at A1. [<a href="#t28">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f29" id="f29"></a>Statement of the Russian Federation President, RG,  Aug.   9, 2008, <em>available  at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.rg.ru/2008/08/09/zayavlenie.html" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.rg.ru/2008/08/  09/zayavlenie.html<span> (external link)</span></a> (last visited Sept. 18, 2008). [<a href="#t29">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f30" id="f30"></a>Sergei Mulin, <em>Palba v Neformalnoi Obstanovke</em> [<em>Shooting  in Unregulated Circumstances</em>] NOVAIA GAZETA, No. 61, Aug. 21, 2008, at 10. [<a href="#t30">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f31" id="f31"></a>Liubov Chizhova, <em>Russian Draftees are Forced to Conclude Military Service Contracts</em>,  RADIO FREE EUROPE/RADIO LIBERTY NEWS REPORT, <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.svobodanews.ru/?Article/2008/08/22/20080%20822181046147.html" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.svobodanews.ru?Article/2008/08/22/20080  822181046147.html<span> (external link)</span></a> (last visited Sept. 17, 2008). 
					[<a href="#t31">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f32" id="f32"></a>Dmitry Medvedev, <em>My ne Dopustim Beznakazannoi Gibeli Sootechestvennikov</em> [<em>We will not Let Our Compatriots Die</em>],  RG, Aug.   9, 2008, at 1. [<a href="#t32">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f33" id="f33"></a>Definition of Aggression, United Nations G.A. Res.  3314, 29th Sess. (Dec. 14, 1974), <em>available at </em><a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/RESOLUTION/GEN/NR0/739/16/IMG/NR073916.pdf?OpenElement" class="external" target="_blank">http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/  RESOLUTION/GEN/NR0/739/16/IMG/NR073916.pdf?OpenElement<span> (external link)</span></a>. [<a href="#t33">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f34" id="f34"></a>BOLESLAW BOCZEK, INTERNATIONAL LAW: A DICTIONARY 412 (Scarecrow Press, 2005). [<a href="#t34">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f35" id="f35"></a>The full text of the Convention is available  online, <em>at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.yale.edu/lawweb/avalon/lawofwar/hague04.htm" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.yale.edu/lawweb/avalon/lawofwar/  hague04.htm<span> (external link)</span></a>. [<a href="#t35">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f36" id="f36"></a>Boris Tuzmakhamedov<em>, Ot Politicheskih Deklaratsii k Pravovym Dovodam </em>[<em>From political declarations to legal  arguments</em>], NEZAVISIMAIA GAZETA,  No. 186, Sept. 2, 2008, at 3. [<a href="#t36">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f37" id="f37"></a>Transcript of the Meeting of the Russian  President with the Members of the International Valdai Club, Sept. 12, 2008, <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.kremlin.ru/eng/speeches/2008/09/12/1644_type82912type82917type84779_206409.shtml" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.kremlin.ru/eng/speeches/2008/09/12/1644_type82912<br/>
					type82917type  84779_206409.shtml<span> (external link)</span></a> (official website of the RF President; last visited  Sept. 18, 2008). [<a href="#t37">Back to Text</a>]<br/>
				</li>
				<li><a name="f38" id="f38"></a>Andreas Umland, <em>A Shield of a Passport</em>, RUSSIA PROFILE, Aug. 21, 2008, published online by ISI Emerging Markets, <em>at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://site.securities.com/" class="external" target="_blank">http://site.securities.com</a> (subscription database; last visited Sept. 24, 2008). 
					[<a href="#t38">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f39" id="f39"></a>Valery Zorkin, <em>Peace Enforcement and Human Rights</em>, RG, Aug. 13, 2008, at 1, <em>available  at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.rg.ru/2008/08/13/zorkin.html" class="external" target="_blank">http://  www.rg.ru/2008/08/13/zorkin.html<span> (external link)</span></a> (last visited Sept. 18, 2008).  Under  Russian law, the authoritative interpretation of the Constitution can be given only  by the Constitutional    Court in  a formal ruling. [<a href="#t39">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f40" id="f40"></a><em>Id</em>.  
					[<a href="#t40">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f41" id="f41"></a><em>Id.</em>, <em>citing </em>SZ  RF 1999, No. 22, Item 2670.  [<a href="#t41">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f42" id="f42"></a><em>Id</em>. [<a href="#t42">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f43" id="f43"></a>Alexander  Osipovich,<em> Controversial Passport Policy Led Russians Into Georgia: Analysts</em>, AGENCE FRANCE-PRESSE, Aug. 21, 2008, <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.hfhrpol.waw.pl/pliki/21August.pdf" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.hfhrpol.waw.pl/pliki/21August.pdf<span> (external link)</span></a> (PDF) (scroll to page 9) (last visited Sept. 24, 2008). 
					[<a href="#t43">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f44" id="f44"></a>1 LEGAL ACTS OF GEORGIA   51 (1998) (the most commonly used translation of  Georgian laws). [<a href="#t44">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f45" id="f45"></a>SZ RF 2002, No. 22, Item 2031.  [<a href="#t45">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f46" id="f46"></a><em>Id</em>. 
					[<a href="#t46">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f47" id="f47"></a><em>South Ossetia Began to Issue Its Own Passports</em>, NOVOSTI RUSSIAN INFORMATION NEWS AGENCY REPORT, Aug. 15, 2006, <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.klerk.ru/more/?55419" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.klerk.ru/more/?55419<span> (external link)</span></a> (last visited Sept. 19, 2008). [<a href="#t47">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f48" id="f48"></a>RG, Aug. 27, 2008, at 1. [<a href="#t48">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f49" id="f49"></a>Alexander Krasulin, <em>Ot Pervogo Litsa</em> [<em>Statements  of the Parliament’s Chairman</em>], PARLAMENTSKAIA GAZETA, No. 52, Aug. 22, 2008, at 3. [<a href="#t49">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f50" id="f50"></a>Declaration on Principles of International Law  Concerning Friendly Relations and Co-Operation among States in accordance with  the Charter of the United Nations, United Nations G.A. Res. 2625, 25th  Sess. (Oct. 24, 1970), <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/RESOLUTION/GEN/NR0/348/90/IMG/NR034890.pdf?OpenElement" class="external" target="_blank">http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/RESOLUTION/GEN/NR0/348/90/IMG/NR034890.pdf?Open  Element<span> (external link)</span></a> (PDF) (last visited Sept. 24, 2008). [<a href="#t50">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f51" id="f51"></a><em>See, e.g., </em>U.N.  Security Council Resolution on the situation in Cyprus, S.C. Res. 1251, U.N.  Doc. S/Res/1251 (June 29, 1999), <em>available  at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/UNDOC/GEN/N99/191/62/PDF/N9919162.pdf?OpenElement" class="external" target="_blank">http://daccessdds.un.org/doc/UNDOC/GEN/N99/191/62/PDF/N9919162.  pdf?OpenElement<span> (external link)</span></a> (PDF) (last visited Sept. 26, 2008), and subsequent resolutions, including the most recent,  S.C. Res. 1818, U.N.Doc. S/Res/1818 (June 13, 2008), <em>available at</em> <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20140716042951/http://www.un.org/Docs/sc/unsc_resolutions08.htm" class="external" target="_blank">http://www.un.org/Docs/sc/unsc_resolutions08.htm<span> (external link)</span></a> (last visited Sept. 26, 2008). [<a href="#t51">Back to Text]</a></li>
				<li><a name="f52" id="f52"></a>Ivan Rodin, <em>Sanktsii  – Ne Problema</em> [<em>Sanctions Are Not a  Problem</em>], NEZAVISIMAIA GAZETA,  No. 186, Sept.   2, 2008, at 1. [<a href="#t52">Back to Text</a>]</li>
				<li><a name="f53" id="f53"></a>All previously established import restrictions  were always explained by sanitary reasons, although they often were politically  motivated. [<a href="#t53">Back to Text</a>]</li>
